definitions.definition: The mental power or ability of choosing ; the will .
examples: Out of all the factors that can influence a person’s decision, none can match the power of his or her own volition .

definitions.definition: A concept that distinguishes whether or not the subject or agent intended something.

main_definition: A conscious choice or decision . [from early 17th c.]
secondary_definitions: The mental power or ability of choosing ; the will .
( linguistics ) A concept that distinguishes whether or not the subject or agent intended something.
